On June 21, 2022, the President signed three bills into law. The first bill, S. 1097, establishes a Federal rotational cyber workforce program for the Federal cyber workforce. The second bill, S. 2520, requires the Department of Homeland Security to increase collaboration with State, local, Tribal, and territorial governments on cybersecurity issues. The third bill, S. 3823, raises certain bankruptcy threshold limits and makes technical corrections to the Bankruptcy Administration Improvement Act. The President thanked various Senators and Representatives for their leadership in passing these bills.